More than 300 of them are orphans because HIV has taken their parents away.
In Esitjeni, the ailments in Swaziland are seen on a smaller scale: the highest rate of HIV infection and the lowest life expectancy in the world, according to UNICEF.
The population almost never accepts male circumcision, a measure that nevertheless guarantees a proven reduction in the risk of infection by half.
More than 40% of the population of Swaziland carries the immunodeficiency virus and it is not uncommon to die in your mid-30s.
