I'm not going to retire, I'm going to die here because the volcano is my whole life.
Although sulfur damages the throat and irritates the eyes when the wind turns and traps the miners in the thick columns of smoke that come out of the volcano, they are so hardened that no one complains of suffering from serious diseases... to which obviously are added their usual breathing problems, osteoarthritis, pains in the knees and shoulders, deformed by the weights.
By balancing the basket on its back, the 53-year-old Unainik can only load 50 kilos.
